<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-8875] CreateTopic API should check topic existence before replication factor</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-8875</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If you try to create a topic and the replication factor cannot be satisfied, Kafka will return `INVALID_REPLICATION_FACTOR`. If the topic already exists, we should probably return `TOPIC_ALREADY_EXISTS` instead. You won&apos;t see this problem if using TopicCommand because we check existence prior to creating the topic.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13254894">KAFKA-8875</key>
